  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  woman with breast cancer histologically proven (group 1), on surveillance of a treated
             breast cancer (group 2) or diagnosis of an detected anomaly

          -  age ≥ 40 years (group 1, group 2); age ≥ 50 years (group 3)

          -  breast size suitable for detector size

          -  possible prior mastectomy

          -  security social covered

          -  signed informed consent

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  breast implant

          -  high genetic risk (mutation)

          -  under justice measures

          -  breast feeding or pregnant woman
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
